.TH XIL\-DAW "1" "2026\-04\-19" "xil\-pipeline 0.1.8" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
xil\-daw
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xil\-daw
[-h] (--episode EPISODE | --tag TAG) [--show SHOW] [--parsed PARSED] [--output-dir OUTPUT_DIR] [--dry-run] [--save-aup3] [--macro] [--timeline] [--timeline-html] [--gap-ms GAP_MS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
DAW Export — export episode as layered WAV files for Audacity

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-episode\fR \fI\,EPISODE\/\fR
Episode tag (e.g. S01E02) — derives cast config, stems, and parsed JSON paths

.TP
\fB\-\-tag\fR \fI\,TAG\/\fR
Raw tag for non\-episodic content (e.g. V01C03, D01)

.TP
\fB\-\-show\fR \fI\,SHOW\/\fR
Show name override (default: from project.json)

.TP
\fB\-\-parsed\fR \fI\,PARSED\/\fR
Path to parsed script JSON (default: parsed/parsed_<slug>_<TAG>.json)

.TP
\fB\-\-output\-dir\fR \fI\,OUTPUT_DIR\/\fR
Output directory for layer WAVs (default: daw/<TAG>/)

.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Show export summary without writing files

.TP
\fB\-\-save\-aup3\fR
Include SaveProject2 step in the Audacity helper script (requires mod\-script\-
pipe)

.TP
\fB\-\-macro\fR
Write an Audacity macro to %APPDATA%\\audacity\\Macros\\ for one\-click import

.TP
\fB\-\-timeline\fR
Print an ASCII timeline visualization of asset placement to stdout

.TP
\fB\-\-timeline\-html\fR
Write an interactive HTML timeline to daw/<TAG>/<TAG>_timeline.html

.TP
\fB\-\-gap\-ms\fR \fI\,GAP_MS\/\fR
Silence gap between foreground stems in ms (default: 600)

